# English-only product language

ModusPractica Pro is an **international app**. All user-facing and project-facing text must be **English (en)**.

## Always write in English

- UI copy: labels, buttons, tooltips, dialogs, toasts, placeholders, empty states
- HTML: `lang="en"`, `<title>`, meta descriptions, headings, body text
- JavaScript: user-visible strings, error messages, confirmations
- Documentation: README, CHANGELOG entries, comments meant for users, release notes
- GitHub: repository description, README, issue/PR text for this project

## Do not add Dutch or other languages

Unless the user explicitly requests a translation or i18n feature, do not introduce non-English UI or docs.

## Locale conventions

- Use international English (en-GB style is fine; match existing copy in the file you edit)
- Dates in UI: follow existing app format (often `DD-MM-YYYY` or ISO as already used)
- Developer chat with the user may be Dutch; **the codebase and app remain English**

## Examples

```html
<!-- BAD -->
<button>Opslaan</button>

<!-- GOOD -->
<button>Save</button>
```

```javascript
// BAD
showToast('Stuk verwijderd');

// GOOD
showToast('Piece deleted');
```
